{
  "name": "03 — Zoom Giveaway Status + Lock + Google Sheet",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 03 — Live status, immutable lock, and transparent Google Sheet\n\nThe database—not Google Sheets—decides eligibility. Locking is atomic and repeat-safe. Google Sheets is created only after the database snapshot exists, then used as the human-readable list beside the creator's browser RNG.\n\nThe manual demo branches use the same production lock and sheet-creation logic.",
        "height": 420,
        "width": 760,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "8aa84811-0cd4-5c4d-b0ef-60e31a5e76d9",
      "name": "WF3 README",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1320,
        -820
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Fill these credentials\n\n1. **Postgres:** same Supabase pooled connection used in Workflows 1 and 2.\n2. **Google Sheets OAuth2:** same credential in `Create Locked Spreadsheet`, `Append Eligible Rows`, and `Protect & Format Spreadsheet`.\n3. **Header Auth:** same credential in both dashboard webhooks. The future webpage sends this header.\n\nNo spreadsheet ID is required—the workflow creates a fresh locked spreadsheet automatically.",
        "height": 420,
        "width": 760,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "55900003-baa5-5b3b-9afb-30260d59072a",
      "name": "WF3 Credentials",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -440,
        -820
      ]
    },
